tv.amwa.maj.model

Interface DataDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DefinitionObject, InterchangeObject, MediaEntity, MetadataObject, WeakReferenceTarget
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataDefinitionImpl

    public interface DataDefinition
extends DefinitionObject

    Specifies a definition for the kind of data that can be stored in a component.

    Section 22.1 of the AAF object specification v1.1 lists the built-in data definitions of the AAF. These can be retrieved by name via the Warehouse.lookup(Class, String) method of the MAJ warehouse.

    See Also:
    DataDefinitionConstant, Warehouse.lookup(Class, String), Dictionary.getDataDefinitions(), Component.getComponentDataDefinition(), OperationDefinition.getOperationDataDefinition(), TypeDefinitions.DataDefinitionWeakReference, TypeDefinitions.DataDefinitionWeakReferenceSet, TypeDefinitions.DataDefinitionWeakReferenceVector, TypeDefinitions.DataDefinitionStrongReference, TypeDefinitions.DataDefinitionStrongReferenceSet

      • doesDataDefConvertTo

        @Bool
boolean doesDataDefConvertTo(DataDefinition dataDefinition)
                            throws NullPointerException

        Returns true if the data represented by this data definition can be converted to the data definition given as an argument. Matching takes place passed on the name property of the data definition.

        Parameters:
        dataDefinition - Data definition to compare this data definition with.
        Returns:
        Can data associated with this data definition be converted into data associated by the given data definition?
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - The given data definition is null.
